x = input("what is your name ?")
print("my name is " + x)
#here x is a variable that stores a value or string or it acts as a container that assigns a value and string
#input() is a function that the user can enter any value or text.
#we use comments for the user in between the parenthesis of the input function.
# + is an operator which adds both the strings
#output will be my name is aman if we put aman in the input
